    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tables with slate surfaces covered with cloth, having six pockets and surrounded by cushioned rails. Distinct from "billiard tables" which do not have pockets.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mesas con superficies de pizarra cubiertas con paño, que tienen seis bolsillos y están rodeadas por barandas acolchadas. Se diferencian de "mesa de billiard” que no tiene bolsillos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tafels met een oppervlak van met stof beklede leistenen platen, met zes zakken en een stootrand rondom. Te onderscheiden van 'biljarttafels' die geen zakken hebben.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
